<subSubSection id="C31BC687FFBAF77FF2C8FA60ECA7D62A" pageId="1" pageNumber="85" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBE950CFFBAF77FF2C8FA60ECA7D62A" blockId="1.[151,1436,1420,1663]" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFBAF77FF2C8FA60EF73D5BA" bold="true" box="[151,267,1420,1446]" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Remarks.</emphasis>
Along with 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFBAF77FF3C9FA60EC10D5BA" authorityName="Kleine" authorityYear="1940" box="[406,616,1420,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudaplatopterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFBAF77FF3C9FA60EC10D5BA" box="[406,616,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Pseudaplatopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B975491EFFBAF77FF0C1FA60ED5DD5BA" box="[670,805,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Kolibaceum</emphasis>
, the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFBAF77FF1FBFA60EA4DD5BA" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1881" box="[932,1077,1420,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Helcophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFBAF77FF1FBFA60EA4DD5BA" box="[932,1077,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Helcophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has both fossil and modern representatives. However, unlike in 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFBAF77FF056FA5CECA3D5D6" authorityName="Kleine" authorityYear="1940" box="[521,731,1456,1482]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudaplatopterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFBAF77FF056FA5CECA3D5D6" box="[521,731,1456,1482]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Pseudaplatopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B975491EFFBAF77FF14CFA5CEDE2D5D6" box="[787,922,1456,1482]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Kolibaceum</emphasis>
, whose living species are referred to separate subgenera (
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFBAF77FF345FA39EC58D5F3" authority="Green, 1951" authorityName="Green" authorityYear="1951" box="[282,544,1492,1519]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Eropterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFBAF77FF345FA39EFF1D5F2" box="[282,393,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Eropterus</emphasis>
Green, 1951
</taxonomicName>
, a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFBAF77FF08DFA38EDDCD5F2" authorityName="Kleine" authorityYear="1940" box="[722,932,1492,1518]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pseudaplatopterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFBAF77FF08DFA38EDDCD5F2" box="[722,932,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Pseudaplatopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFBAF77FF1BBFA38EB6CD5F2" authority="Kazantsev, 1990" authorityName="Kazantsev" authorityYear="1990" box="[996,1300,1492,1519]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Laterialis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFBAF77FF1BBFA38EA29D5F2" box="[996,1105,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Laterialis</emphasis>
Kazantsev, 1990
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFBAF77FF712FA39EFCFD60E" authority="Kazantsev, 1997" authorityName="Kazantsev" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Tricostaeptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFBAF77FF712FA39EE8CD60E" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Tricostaeptera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF90E8FDFFBAF77FF2A4FA15EFCFD60E" author="Kazantsev, S. V." box="[251,439,1528,1555]" pageId="1" pageNumber="85" pagination="159 - 164" refId="ref2635" refString="Kazantsev, S. V. (1997) A recent species of the fossil genus Kolibaceum Winkler (Coleoptera, Lycidae) from Eastern China. Entomologica Basiliensia, 20, 159 - 164." type="journal article" year="1997">Kazantsev, 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, subgenera of 
<emphasis id="B975491EFFBAF77FF006FA14EC98D60E" box="[601,736,1528,1554]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Kolibaceum</emphasis>
), both extinct and extant species have been discovered in both subgenera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C01EE8FFFBAF77FF371F9F0EFC7D62A" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1881" box="[302,447,1564,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Helcophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFBAF77FF371F9F0EFC7D62A" box="[302,447,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Helcophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF90E8FDFFBAF77FF392F9F0ECF3D62B" author="Kazantsev, S. V." box="[461,651,1564,1591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="85" pagination="383 - 389" refId="ref2761" refString="Kazantsev, S. V. (2015) New taxa of Helcophorus Fairmaire, 1891, with a key to species of the genus (Coleoptera: Lycidae). In: Hartmann, M. &amp; Weipert, J. (Eds.), Biodiversitat und Naturausstattung im Himalaya. Band 5. Verein der Freunde &amp; Forderer des Naturkundemuseums Erfurt e. V., Erfurt, pp. 383 - 389." type="book chapter" year="2015">Kazantsev, 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF90E8FDFFBAF77FF0C8F9F0ECACD62A" author="Kazantsev, S. V." box="[663,724,1564,1590]" pageId="1" pageNumber="85" pagination="377 - 387" refId="ref2897" refString="Kazantsev, S. V. (2020) First fossil representative of the net-winged beetles genus Plateros Bourgeois, 1879 (Insecta: Coleoptera: Lycidae) from Mexican amber, with redescription of Electropteron avus gen. n., sp. n. from Dominican amber and a note on the time of origin of the family. Russian Entomological Journal, 29 (4), 377 - 387. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / rusentj. 29.4.04" type="journal article" year="2020">2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31BC687FFBAF77FF298F9ACEF47D663" pageId="1" pageNumber="85" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BBE950CFFBAF77FF298F9ACEF47D663" blockId="1.[151,1436,1420,1663]" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis id="B975491EFFBAF77FF298F9ACEF19D646" bold="true" box="[199,353,1600,1626]" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Distribution.</emphasis>
Southeast of Palaearctic and north of Oriental realms. Fossil taxa known from Baltic and 
<collectingRegion id="49C55BEEFFBAF77FF70EF9ADEBE4D647" box="[1361,1436,1601,1627]" country="Ukraine" name="Rivne" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Rovno</collectingRegion>
amber (
<figureCitation id="133A8989FFBAF77FF2B3F988EF49D663" box="[236,305,1636,1663]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1509,1533]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1484]" captionTargetId="figure-24@5.[151,1436,181,1484]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Map of distribution of Helcophorus species: orange circles – H. (s. str.) species; red-and-black circles – H. (Thibeteros) species (after Kazantsev, 2015, modified)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6498083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6498083/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="85">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
